<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-30T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60F31/185: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wright</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-30T16:00:00+01:00">March 30, 1937—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 30—12:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>16. Your telegram No. 6, March 27, 2 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d169fn8">Not printed.</note> Proposal for undertaking of trade agreement
                                negotiations discussed today with Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="9" xml:id="d169fn9">K. Krofta.</note> and Chief of Economic
                                Section Foreign Office and copy of <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> given to each. Czech Legation has reported
                                receipt of your note and immediate consideration of matter is
                                promised.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>